Key Architectural Decisions & Why
Several decisions in the original roadmap have been optimized based on production experience:

Decision
Rationale
Supabase over raw AWS
Supabase combines PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage + Realtime in one managed service. This eliminates 3 separate AWS services for early phases, reducing ops burden. Migrate to raw RDS only when you exceed 50K students.
Single vector namespace
Original roadmap stored FAISS indexes per student locally. Switch to Pinecone with student_id + subject as namespace. Avoids S3 I/O for index re-loads on every query — 10x faster retrieval.
Structured state via Redis
Session state machine stored in Redis as JSON, keyed by session_id. Allows stateless backend pods — any ECS instance can handle any WebSocket. Critical for auto-scaling.
Whisper streaming (VAD)
Original roadmap sends full audio blobs. Replace with 200ms VAD (Voice Activity Detection) chunks. Reduces transcription latency from ~2s to ~400ms. Students feel heard instantly.
MediaPipe off main thread
Run MediaPipe in a Web Worker, not the main thread. Original code blocks UI rendering at 10fps. Web Worker approach gives true 10fps CV without janky sessions.
ELO seeded from test score
Don't start all students at ELO 1000. Seed from onboarding diagnostic score. Students get correctly-pitched questions from session 1, not after 5 wrong answers.

