PHASE 3  │  Teaching Engine, Voice & Real-Time Sessions
Weeks 7–10     ·   State machine · GPT-4o · Whisper VAD · ElevenLabs · WebSocket

Goal
Build the core product — the interactive AI tutor. This is the feature students will use for hours daily. Quality here directly determines user retention. The teaching engine must feel like a patient, knowledgeable human teacher — not a chatbot.

Teaching State Machine — Optimized
State
AI Behavior
GREET
First turn. AI greets student by name, asks what chapter they want to study today. Loads teaching context.
EXPLAIN
Delivers concept in 2-3 sentences max. Uses simple language for the student's grade. Pauses naturally.
QUESTION
Asks exactly ONE focused check-in question. Never multi-part. Calibrated to current ELO difficulty.
WAIT
Silent listening state. 8-second silence timeout triggers a gentle prompt: 'Take your time…'
EVALUATE
Scores student response: CORRECT / PARTIAL / WRONG. Logs ELO delta.
PRAISE
On CORRECT: warm, specific praise ('You got the key point — the chlorophyll absorbs light'). Advance topic.
SIMPLIFY
On PARTIAL: acknowledge what was right, re-explain the gap differently. One more attempt.
RETEACH
On 2 consecutive WRONG: completely different angle (analogy, real-world example). Lower ELO by 15.
DOUBT
Student asks a question (detected via '?' or question words). Answer from RAG. Return to prior state.
SUMMARY
End of session: 3-point summary of what was covered. Preview of next session's topic.

