Goal
Detect attention lapses (gaze-away, phone use, absence from frame) using computer vision, log incidents with screenshots, and notify parents in real time. Privacy is non-negotiable: raw video never leaves the browser.

Privacy-First Architecture

🔑  CRITICAL: Legal requirement: show a 'Camera active — behavior is being monitored' banner at all times during session. Store explicit consent record with timestamp in DB. Without consent, monitoring must not activate.

Data
Handling
Raw video
NEVER sent to server. Stays in browser MediaStream.
MediaPipe
Runs in a Web Worker (not main thread). Prevents UI jank during CV processing.
Frame sampling
Analyze 1 frame per second (not 10fps). Sufficient for detection, 10x cheaper CPU.
Snapshots
Low-res JPEG (320×240) captured only on incident trigger. Not stored unless incident confirmed.
